  "prompt": "What's your definition of \"friends\"?",
  "response": "The term \"friends\" typically refers to individuals who share a mutual bond of affection, trust, and support. Friends are people with whom one feels comfortable, valued, and understood, often sharing common interests, experiences, or values. A healthy friendship is characterized by:\n\n1. **Trust**: The ability to rely on each other and feel secure in the relationship.  \n2. **Respect**: Valuing each other\u2019s opinions, boundaries, and individuality.  \n3. **Empathy**: Understanding and sharing in each other\u2019s feelings and experiences.  \n4. **Support**: Being there for one another during both good and challenging times.  \n5. **Reciprocity**: A balanced give-and-take in the relationship, where both parties contribute equally.  \n6. **Honesty**: Open and truthful communication, even when it\u2019s difficult.  \n\nFriendships can vary in depth and closeness\u2014some may be casual and based on shared activities, while others are deeply emotional and long-lasting. Ultimately, true friends are those who enrich your life and stand by you through thick and thin.",
